@node "Pref2" "P 2"


This menus are available:


@{"Project" link "Project" 0} @{"Pref 1" link "Pref1" 0} @{"P 2" link "Pref2" 0} @{"P 3" link "Pref3" 0} @{"Precision" link "Precision" 0} @{"Layouts" link "Layouts" 0} @{"Konfiguration" link "Konfiguration" 0}
                @{u}   @{uu}


Different timezones from -11 to +12 hours based on Greenvich Mean Time(GMT).
@{b}@{u}Attention:@{ub}@{uu} The Swatch Beats are based on @{b}BMT@{ub} (Biel Mean Time), a town in
Swizerland. A Day in internet-time begins at 00:00h BMT with @000. For
example the configuration for  Berlin is: GMT +1 - DST On.  London: GMT +-0,
DST On. New York: GMT -5, DST On
@endnode

@node "Pref3" "P 3"


This menus are available:


@{"Project" link "Project" 0} @{"Pref 1" link "Pref1" 0} @{"P 2" link "Pref2" 0} @{"P 3" link "Pref3" 0} @{"Precision" link "Precision" 0} @{"Layouts" link "Layouts" 0} @{"Konfiguration" link "Konfiguration" 0}
                     @{u}   @{uu}


Some examples configurations.


Attention:

This ist not a wordlclock-function.  It will only change the calculation
base for the Swatch-Beats.

If you want to see some worldtimes press >left Amiga A<.
@endnode

@node "Precision" "Precision"


This menus are available:


@{"Project" link "Project" 0} @{"Pref 1" link "Pref1" 0} @{"P 2" link "Pref2" 0} @{"P 3" link "Pref3" 0} @{"Precision" link "Precision" 0} @{"Layouts" link "Layouts" 0} @{"Konfiguration" link "Konfiguration" 0}
                        @{u}          @{uu}


With this option you can set up the claculation precision. Only available in
Amiga-Beats. The original Swatch-Beats have three counters, without decimal
values. This is like no seconds visible on your clock. This is not good,
isn`t it ? So I have a @{"Idea" link "Idee_uebernehmen" 0} and added this fine function. I prefer two
decimal values. I call them beaties ;-))
@endnode

